<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="353" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[160,1156,1070,1270]" box="[160,276,1070,1096]" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,1070,1096]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[160,1156,1070,1270]" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">
The new species can be readily distinguished by distinctive traits that are absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="du Buysson" authorityYear="1909" box="[160,308,1142,1166]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="353" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentinum">
<emphasis box="[160,308,1142,1166]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">H. argentinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
such as: second tarsomere of metaleg with double line of spines; metabasitarsus with apical crown of spines; mesoscutal integument rugulose to striate anterolaterally; fore wing entirely setose; apical margin of T3 with narrow translucent edge; compound eyes with sparse short microtrichia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
