<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="356" pageId="3" pageNumber="353" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="3.[160,1156,1320,1727]" lastBlockId="6.[160,1156,142,478]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="356" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,561,1355,1381]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">
<typeStatus box="[160,267,1355,1381]" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">Holotype</typeStatus>
female (
<figureCitation box="[383,482,1355,1381]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1415,1438]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., holotype female. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e) Paratype ♀, scanning electron micrographs of head, frontal view. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178253/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(a–d)).
</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[577,683,1357,1381]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">Body size</emphasis>
: 3.6 mm (
<figureCitation box="[813,905,1357,1381]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1415,1438]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., holotype female. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e) Paratype ♀, scanning electron micrographs of head, frontal view. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178253/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(a)). 
<emphasis box="[965,1079,1357,1381]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">Coloration</emphasis>
: body predominantly light green with purplish blue bands on dorsum; head green with purplish blue stain among ocelli (
<figureCitation box="[546,635,1426,1450]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1415,1438]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., holotype female. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e) Paratype ♀, scanning electron micrographs of head, frontal view. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178253/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(b)); scape greenish; pedicel brownish; flagellomeres brown; mandible brown; mesosoma primarily light green, with bluish tint on pronotum; golden highlights on dorsum of pronotum and metasoma; mesoscutellum, metanotum and propodeum with dark band covering much of disc; dark band covering the mesoscutum (
<figureCitation box="[365,453,1565,1589]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1415,1438]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., holotype female. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e) Paratype ♀, scanning electron micrographs of head, frontal view. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178253/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(b)); tegula brown; coxae and femora green; trochanters light brown; tibiae green; tarsi light brown; sterna brown; T1 light green with golden highlights; T2 light green marginally, with dark blue band occupying much of disc (
<figureCitation box="[1062,1155,1634,1658]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1415,1438]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., holotype female. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e) Paratype ♀, scanning electron micrographs of head, frontal view. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178253/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(d)); T3 light green with reddish shine. 
<emphasis box="[629,686,1669,1693]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">Head</emphasis>
: scapal basin densely marked by crossridging (
<figureCitation box="[257,344,1703,1727]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1415,1438]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., holotype female. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e) Paratype ♀, scanning electron micrographs of head, frontal view. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178253/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="353">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(c)), without setae; compound eye with microtrichia among ommatidia (as in 
<figureCitation box="[226,311,1565,1589]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1415,1438]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., holotype female. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e) Paratype ♀, scanning electron micrographs of head, frontal view. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178253/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="354">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(e)); malar space short, less than 0.2 × MOD; subantennal space 0.6 × MOD; clypeal margin straight; mandible with sub-medial tooth (as in 
<figureCitation box="[907,998,1599,1623]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1415,1438]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., holotype female. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e) Paratype ♀, scanning electron micrographs of head, frontal view. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178253/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="354">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(e)); F1 1.3 × longer than F2; genal margin without definite carina, with somewhat irregular ridge. 
<emphasis box="[160,208,1669,1693]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="354">Legs</emphasis>
: tarsal claw with single perpendicular submedial tooth; metabasitarsus with crown of spines apically; second tarsomere of metaleg with double line of spines on ventral surface; metafemur enlarged. 
<emphasis box="[513,579,1456,1480]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Wings</emphasis>
: fore wing entirely setose (as in 
<figureCitation box="[981,1079,1456,1480]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1250,1273]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1201]" captionTargetId="figure-94@5.[178,1138,142,1218]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., paratype male. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e–g) Genital capsule. (e) Ventral view. (f) Lateral view. (g) Dorsal view. (h) Fore wing. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, h, 0.5 mm; e–g, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178255/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Figure 2</figureCitation>
(h)); M gently curved, almost straight, arising slightly after 1cu-a; Rs short, evenly curved, tubular proximally, fading distally; A1 tubular at cu-a intersection, fading gradually. 
<emphasis box="[160,268,1560,1584]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Pronotum</emphasis>
: clearly narrower than head; medial notch slightly marked; anterolateral margin discretely carinate; lateral depression roughly sculptured. 
<emphasis box="[922,1058,1595,1619]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Mesoscutum</emphasis>
: integument somewhat rugulose, striate anterolaterally; notauli deeply impressed; parapsidal lines discrete, surrounded by punctures. 
<emphasis box="[637,777,1664,1688]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Mesopleuron</emphasis>
: round, gently deflected posteriorly, with discrete scratch marks, scrobe deeply marked. 
<emphasis box="[838,998,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="355">Mesoscutellum</emphasis>
: one-third as long as mesoscutum. 
<emphasis box="[413,540,142,166]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="356">Metanotum</emphasis>
: posterior margin convex, as long as mesoscutellum. 
<emphasis box="[160,285,177,201]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="356">Propodeum</emphasis>
: dorsal surface macro-foveolate, V-shaped; lateral process with some striate marks both dorsolaterally and lateroventrally; lateral process pointed apically. 
<emphasis box="[1035,1149,212,236]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="356">Metasoma</emphasis>
: T3 with narrow apical translucent edge; margins smooth, round, without notch or corners; S1 polished; S2–S3 with silvery semi-decumbent setae. 
<emphasis box="[896,1014,281,305]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="356">Punctation</emphasis>
: head regularly punctate, changing abruptly in the scapal basin, which is densely striated (as in 
<figureCitation box="[160,246,350,374]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1415,1438]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[178,1138,142,1384]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., holotype female. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e) Paratype ♀, scanning electron micrographs of head, frontal view. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178253/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="356">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(e)); mesosoma mostly foveate, with some rugulose and striate areas marginally; metasoma with integument predominantly puncticulate, with discrete striate marks laterally on T2 and entirely on T3; T1–T2 finely punctate, distinctly shallower than the rest of body, with broad shiny interspaces among well-separated punctures.
</paragraph>
