<paragraph blockId="6.[160,1156,522,825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,425,522,548]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="356">
Male (
<figureCitation box="[244,350,522,548]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1250,1273]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1201]" captionTargetId="figure-94@5.[178,1138,142,1218]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., paratype male. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e–g) Genital capsule. (e) Ventral view. (f) Lateral view. (g) Dorsal view. (h) Fore wing. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, h, 0.5 mm; e–g, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178255/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="356">Figure 2</figureCitation>
(a–h)).
</emphasis>
Similar to female, except: distinct bronze shine on frons (
<figureCitation box="[167,268,558,582]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1250,1273]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1201]" captionTargetId="figure-94@5.[178,1138,142,1218]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., paratype male. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e–g) Genital capsule. (e) Ventral view. (f) Lateral view. (g) Dorsal view. (h) Fore wing. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, h, 0.5 mm; e–g, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178255/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="356">Figure 2</figureCitation>
(c)), pronotum, mesoscutum and T1–T2 (
<figureCitation box="[764,864,558,582]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1250,1273]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1201]" captionTargetId="figure-94@5.[178,1138,142,1218]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., paratype male. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e–g) Genital capsule. (e) Ventral view. (f) Lateral view. (g) Dorsal view. (h) Fore wing. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, h, 0.5 mm; e–g, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178255/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="356">Figure 2</figureCitation>
(a)); mesosoma primarily green blue, with bluish highlights on pronotum, mesoscutellum, metanotum and propodeum; large dark blue band covering the mesoscutum (
<figureCitation box="[931,1034,628,652]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1250,1273]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1201]" captionTargetId="figure-94@5.[178,1138,142,1218]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., paratype male. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e–g) Genital capsule. (e) Ventral view. (f) Lateral view. (g) Dorsal view. (h) Fore wing. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, h, 0.5 mm; e–g, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178255/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="356">Figure 2</figureCitation>
(b)); tibiae brownish green; T1 light green marginally, with dark blue band on disc; T2 light green marginally, with large dark blue band occupying much of disc (
<figureCitation box="[979,1076,697,721]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1250,1273]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1201]" captionTargetId="figure-94@5.[178,1138,142,1218]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., paratype male. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e–g) Genital capsule. (e) Ventral view. (f) Lateral view. (g) Dorsal view. (h) Fore wing. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, h, 0.5 mm; e–g, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178255/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="356">Figure 2</figureCitation>
(d)); T3 light green with bluish tint on disc; metafemur not so enlarged as in females; genital capsule (
<figureCitation box="[269,371,766,790]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1250,1273]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1201]" captionTargetId="figure-94@5.[178,1138,142,1218]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Hedychridium periotoi Lucena sp. nov., paratype male. (a) Habitus, lateral view. (b) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (c) Head, frontal view. (d) Metasoma, dorsal view. (e–g) Genital capsule. (e) Ventral view. (f) Lateral view. (g) Dorsal view. (h) Fore wing. Scale bars: a, b, 1 mm; c, d, h, 0.5 mm; e–g, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5178255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5178255/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="356">Figure 2</figureCitation>
(e–g)), gonocoxal lobes widely fused dorsally, lobes as long as aedeagus; cuspis with long apical setae.
</paragraph>
